<h3>Public Transit Reality</h3>
<div class="consequence-text"><p>You commit to using public transportation. This includes the Chicago "L" and (Chicago Transit Authority) CTA bus service. It's the most affordable option, and you'll make it work.</p><p>The bus and train system can get you close to the work sites, though not exactly where you always need to be.</p><p>It's cheaper than alternatives, but there are risks. The Chicago Police Department (CPD) are more likely to question people carrying large bags or work equipment.</p></div>
<hr>
<div class="consequence-text"><p>Now you need to decide how you will structure your work schedule once you get to the job areas:</p></div>
<<link "Continue">><<goto "PublicTransitChoice">><</link>>

